{"type":"message","id":"024d4ad3","parentId":"be089221","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:01:38.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering malware inspection skills**\n\nI'm thinking about proposing skills that can inspect for malware, like a “malware scanner” or “security audit” skill. From the ClawHub list, I don’t see any dedicated malware scanner, just skills like “openclaw-safety-coach” and “fact-checker.” I could suggest searching for related terms or examining the metadata and code of candidate skills, though I can’t scan external code. I should also clarify if the user wants static analysis or a malware scan runner and suggest creating a bespoke “malware-scan” skill if needed.**Planning malware inspection skills**\n\nThe user asked for a skill that can inspect for malware, so I need to respond with a clear plan and confirm the scope. I might suggest using ClawHub with the 'inspect' subcommand to fetch the skill's metadata and files. Additionally, I can propose setting up a safety workflow that scans scripts for suspicious patterns and checks for any network calls. I want to keep my response concise and focused on the user's needs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Great idea. Since there aren’t obvious off-the-shelf “malware scan” skills, here’s how we can get you what you want:\n\nWhat I can do now\n- Identify candidate security-focused skills that could help with vetting others (e.g., openclaw-safety-coach, fact-checker) and inspect their capabilities.\n- Fetch and inspect the code/files of a chosen skill to look for red flags (suspicious network calls, hardcoded secrets, obfuscated code).\n- Propose or help assemble a lightweight malware-scan workflow you can run on a skill’s scripts (static checks, pattern scans, permission requests).\n\nRecommended approach\n1) Pick candidates to inspect\n- openclaw-safety-coach (safety-focused, may include policy checks)\n- fact-checker (content integrity checks)\n- traffic-data or other security-related skills you’ve installed (for reference)\n\n2) Inspect the candidate’s files\n- Use clawhub inspect <slug> to fetch metadata and files, then review scripts (e.g., shell, Python, JS) for:\n  - Unusual network activity\n  - Access to secrets or keys\n  - Code that downloads/executes other code\n  - Obfuscated or base64-encoded payloads\n  - Excessive file system or process privileges\n\n3) If gaps exist, we can itemize a malware-scan routine:\n- Static checks: search for suspicious patterns (base64, eval, exec, system calls)\n- Dependency review: verify legitimate packages and hashes\n- Permission audit: ensure minimal required permissions\n- Integrity markers: compare hashes of key files against known-good references\n\nWhat would you like to do next?\n- I can inspect one or more specific skills (give me the slug, e.g., openclaw-safety-coach) and report back on potential malware signals.\n- Or I can fetch metadata for a few security-related skills and propose a short malware-scan checklist you can run locally."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":557,"output":927,"cacheRead":15744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17228,"cost":{"input":-557,"output":-927,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1484}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772143288038}}
