{"type":"message","id":"38762a87","parentId":"8affae00","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:07:42.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing prompt examples**\n\nI should give the user some concrete examples of how to use MV-SKILL for inspecting a skill. Since MV-SKILL is a file in the workspace, I'll detail a natural language prompt along with the corresponding CLI commands, such as `clawhub inspect <slug>` and running `static_scan.sh` to generate a report. I'll outline the role: \"MV-SKILL: Malware Vetting Skill\" and use an example slug like \"traffic-data\". My steps will include selecting the slug, running the inspect command, executing the static scan script, and generating a report. I'll keep it concise and include sample scripts without needing any tool calls.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Here are ready-to-use prompts you can give MV-SKILL to inspect a specific skill, using the workflow in SKILLS.md.\n\nExample 1: Quick static vet of a single skill (traffic-data)\n- Prompt: “Inspect the skill traffic-data for malware using MV-SKILL. Fetch metadata with clawhub inspect, run a static string-based scan for red flags, audit dependencies, and produce a Findings Report.”\n\nWhat MV-SKILL would do (high level)\n- Run: clawhub inspect traffic-data > inspect_traffic-data_metadata.txt\n- Create a local workspace: mkdir -p ~/inspection/workspace/traffic-data\n- Run a static scan (example steps MV-SKILL would embed):\n  - grep -RIn for suspicious patterns (exec, system, base64, wget, curl, etc.) in the skill files\n  - List dependencies from requirements.txt and package.json if present\n  - Compute hashes of key files and compare to any known-good references (if you have a baseline)\n- Produce a Findings Report (Markdown or text) with:\n  - Scope, artifacts inspected, evidence, risk rating\n  - Recommendations (install safely, request code review, or avoid)\n\nExample 2: Vet multiple skills in one go\n- Prompt: “Vet the following slugs with MV-SKILL: traffic-data, openclaw-safety-coach. For each, inspect metadata, run static checks, review dependencies, and output separate Findings sections in a single Malware Vetting Report.”\n\nWhat MV-SKILL would do\n- Loop over slugs, for each:\n  - clawhub inspect <slug> > inspect_<slug>_metadata.txt\n  - Run static_scan.sh or inline grep-assisted checks\n  - Append a section to Findings.md with the slug, findings, risk, and remediation\n\nExample 3: Generate a ready-made command bundle\n- Prompt: “Create a ready-made malware vetting bundle for slug traffic-data, including: a) inspect command, b) static_scan.sh, c) findings-template.md, d) a sample findings.md with placeholders.”\n- MV-SKILL outcome:\n  - inspect_traffic-data_metadata.txt\n  - inspect/traffic-data/static_scan.sh\n  - findings-template.md\n  - findings_traffic-data.md filled with placeholders\n\nExample 4: Request an audit summary\n- Prompt: “Provide a concise malware-vetting summary for traffic-data after static review, including key flags found (if any), dependencies reviewed, and a remediation recommendation.”\n- MV-SKILL output: a short executive summary with risk rating and next steps\n\nTips for best results\n- Use a precise slug for the target skill (e.g., traffic-data) to avoid ambiguity.\n- If you have a baseline of known-good files, share hashes so MV-SKILL can compare against them.\n- If you want a full automated bundle, ask MV-SKILL to output:\n  - A Findings.md (comprehensive)\n  - A Findings-summary.md (executive-friendly)\n  - A static_scan.sh tailored to the slug\n  - An artifact bundle directory with all inspected files\n\nWant me to craft a specific, copy-paste prompt for your current target slug (e.g., traffic-data or openclaw-safety-coach) and include exact CLI commands you can paste to run? If yes, tell me the slug and preferred output format (Markdown, plain text, or both)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":1358,"output":987,"cacheRead":19328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21673,"cost":{"input":-1358,"output":-987,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-2345}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772143656044}}
