{"type":"message","id":"0183d781","parentId":"fca3f727","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:10:33.397Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing Script Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on the core of the script itself. My current line of thinking is how to effectively call and utilize the MV-SKILL from within a shell script to inspect multiple skills as requested.\n\n**Building Script Logic**\n\nMy focus has shifted to the practical implementation of the script. I'm currently devising the most efficient way to integrate the MV-SKILL commands for inspecting multiple provided skills within a shell script environment.\n\n**Automating Skill Inspections**\n\nI'm now focusing on the practical scripting aspect. My current thought process involves translating the outlined MV-SKILL inspection steps into an automated shell script, specifically targeting the example of vetting multiple slugs and consolidating findings into a single report.\n\n**Implementing Script Logic**\n\nMy focus is now on translating the outlined steps into a functional shell script. I'm working on iterating through the provided slugs, invoking `clawhub inspect`, performing the requested static and dependency checks, and consolidating all findings into a single, comprehensive report.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Okay, this is a great idea: creating a reusable script that embodies the Malware Vetting Skill workflow. This will make it much easier to inspect multiple skills.\n\nHere's a shell script you can save (e.g., as `vet-clawhub-skill.sh`) that automates the process. It implements the steps outlined in your SKILLS.md.\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n# Malware Vetting Script (MVS) for ClawHub Skills\n# Embodies the workflow from ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/SKILLS.md\n\nset -euo pipefail # Exit on error, unset variable, or pipe failure\n\nreadonly SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$(readlink -f \"$0\")\")\"\nreadonly INSPECTION_BASE_DIR=\"$HOME/inspection/workspace\"\nreadonly CLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\" # Assuming this is the root of your OpenClaw installation\n\n# --- Configuration ---\n# Add file extensions to scan for code patterns (e.g., .py, .js, .sh, .ts)\n# Add new ones if you encounter them in skills.\nCODE_EXTENSIONS=(\"sh\" \"py\" \"js\" \"ts\" \"bash\" \"json\" \"cfg\" \"conf\")\n# Patterns to search for in static analysis (basic red flags)\n# More exhaustive list can be added here.\n# Includes: eval, exec, system calls, base64 encoding, network requests,\n# hardcoded secrets patterns, etc.\nSUSPICIOUS_PATTERNS=\\\n\"(exec\\(|system\\(|eval\\(|base64|decode\\(|wget|curl|openssl|http|https|proxy|secret|key=|token=|password=|client_id=|client_secret|api_key=|api-key=|AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID|password_hash|oauth|private_key|certificate|ssh_key|private-key|cert=.+|privkey=.+|--eval|'eval'|download=|upload=|post=|https://)\"\n\n# --- Helper Functions ---\n\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $@\"\n}\n\nerror() {\n    log \"ERROR: $@\" >&2\n    exit 1\n}\n\nwarn() {\n    log \"WARNING: $@\" >&2\n}\n\n# Function to create a temporary scratch dir for specific checks\ncreate_scratch_dir() {\n    local slug=\"$1\"\n    local scratch_dir=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/scratch\"\n    mkdir -p \"$scratch_dir\"\n    echo \"$scratch_dir\"\n}\n\n# Function to create a basic findings report file for a slug\ncreate_slug_report() {\n    local slug=\"$1\"\n    local report_file=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n    # Clear previous report for this slug if it exists\n    rm -f \"$report_file\"\n    log \"Creating report file for ${slug}: ${report_file}\"\n    echo \"# Malware Vetting Report: \\`${slug}\\`\" > \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Scope\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- Skill: \\`${slug}\\`\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- Inspected By: MVS Script (Automated)\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- Timestamp: \\$(date +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Artifacts Examined\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- Fetched via: \\`clawhub inspect ${slug}\\`\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"  - Metadata saved to: \\`${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/inspect_${slug}_metadata.txt\\`\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"  - Skill files archived in: \\`${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/artifact_bundle/\\`\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Static Findings (Red Flags)\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"_(Listing suspicious patterns found in code files. 'OK' means no patterns matched.)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Dependency Review\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"_(Summary of dependencies found and basic audit status.)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Secrets Exposure Check\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"_(Search for hardcoded secrets like API keys, tokens, passwords.)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Permissions and Privilege Review\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"_(Assessment of requested permissions and potential privilege escalation.)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Integrity Checks (Hashing)\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"_(Hashing of key files for integrity verification.)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Risk Assessment\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"**Summary:** _(This section will be filled based on findings. E.g., LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH RISK)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"## Recommendations\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- **Recommendation:** _(e.g., INSTALL SAFELY, REQUEST CODE REVIEW, AVOID INSTALL, ISOLATE & RE-SCAN)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"- Next Steps: _(e.g., Follow up on specific findings, perform dynamic analysis)_\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"---\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"### Appendix: Commands Run and Outputs\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n\n    echo \"$report_file\"\n}\n\n# Function to perform static code analysis\nperform_static_analysis() {\n    local slug=\"$1\"\n    local skill_files_dir=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/artifact_bundle\"\n    local report_file=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n    local scratch_dir=$(create_scratch_dir \"$slug\")\n    local static_scan_log=\"${scratch_dir}/static_scan_grep.log\"\n\n    log \"Performing static analysis for ${slug}...\"\n    echo \"#### Static Scan Findings (Red Flags)\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo '```bash' >> \"$report_file\"\n\n    # Ensure clawhub inspect was successful and files were downloaded\n    if [ ! -d \"$skill_files_dir\" ] || [ -z \"$(ls -A \"$skill_files_dir\")\" ]; then\n        warn \"Skill files for ${slug} not found or empty at ${skill_files_dir}. Skipping static analysis.\"\n        echo \"Skill files not found or empty. Skipping static analysis.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        echo '```' >> \"$report_file\"\n        return\n    fi\n\n    # Construct grep command to search across specified code extensions\n    local find_args=\"\"\n    for ext in \"${CODE_EXTENSIONS[@]}\"; do\n        find_args+=\"-name '*.${ext}' -o \"\n    done\n    # Remove trailing ' -o '\n    find_args=${find_args% -o }\n\n    # Using find to recursively search for files with specified extensions\n    # and then piping to grep for patterns\n    # The '|| true' at the end prevents exit if grep finds nothing (exit code 1)\n    if find \"$skill_files_dir\" -type f \\( $find_args \\) -print0 | xargs -0 grep -iEn --color=never \"$SUSPICIOUS_PATTERNS\" 2>/dev/null > \"$static_scan_log\"; then\n        if [ -s \"$static_scan_log\" ]; then\n            cat \"$static_scan_log\" >> \"$report_file\"\n            echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n            echo \"--- SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND ---\" >> \"$report_file\"\n            echo \"Review lines marked with suspicious patterns.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        else\n            echo \"✅ No obvious suspicious patterns found based on current search criteria.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        fi\n    else\n        warn \"grep command failed or found no matches for ${slug}. Check script or file permissions.\"\n        echo \"WARNING: grep scan encountered issues or found no matches. Manual review needed.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    fi\n\n    echo '```' >> \"$report_file\"\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n}\n\n# Function to inspect dependencies\ninspect_dependencies() {\n    local slug=\"$1\"\n    local skill_files_dir=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/artifact_bundle\"\n    local report_file=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n    local scratch_dir=$(create_scratch_dir \"$slug\")\n\n    log \"Inspecting dependencies for ${slug}...\"\n    echo \"#### Dependency Review\" >> \"$report_file\"\n\n    local python_deps_found=false\n    local node_deps_found=false\n\n    if [ -f \"${skill_files_dir}/requirements.txt\" ]; then\n        log \"Found requirements.txt for ${slug}. Logging:\"\n        echo \"Found \\`requirements.txt\\`. Output from \\`pip freeze\\` (or similar):\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        echo '```bash' >> \"$report_file\"\n        # Try to install in a temporary env and freeze, or just list them\n        # For simplicity here, just display the file content for manual review\n        if [ -f \"${skill_files_dir}/requirements.txt\" ]; then\n            cat \"${skill_files_dir}/requirements.txt\" >> \"$report_file\"\n            python_deps_found=true\n        else\n            echo \"No requirements.txt found.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        fi\n        echo '```' >> \"$report_file\"\n    fi\n\n    if [ -f \"${skill_files_dir}/package.json\" ]; then\n        log \"Found package.json for ${slug}. Logging:\"\n        echo \"Found \\`package.json\\`. Output from \\`npm ls --json\\` (if npm available):\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        echo '```bash' >> \"$report_file\"\n        if [ -f \"${skill_files_dir}/package.json\" ]; then\n            # Attempt to run `npm ls --json` if npm is available and works in this env\n            # This might fail if node/npm are not available in the execution environment\n            if command -v npm &> /dev/null; then\n                pushd \"${skill_files_dir}\" > /dev/null\n                # Use npm ci for deterministic builds for review, or just ls\n                # CI is safer as it avoids using potentially malicious install scripts\n                if npm ci --ignore-scripts --force --no-audit --prefer-offline &> /dev/null; then\n                    npm ls --json --all --long --production --omit=dev 2>/dev/null | tee -a \"$report_file\"\n                else\n                    echo \"Could not run 'npm ci'. Displaying package.json content instead.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n                    cat \"${skill_files_dir}/package.json\" >> \"$report_file\"\n                fi\n                popd > /dev/null\n                node_deps_found=true\n            else\n                echo \"Node/npm not found. Displaying package.json content for manual review.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n                cat \"${skill_files_dir}/package.json\" >> \"$report_file\"\n                node_deps_found=true\n            fi\n        else\n            echo \"No package.json found.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        fi\n        echo '```' >> \"$report_file\"\n    fi\n\n    if ! $python_deps_found && ! $node_deps_found; then\n        echo \"✅ No common dependency manifest files (requirements.txt, package.json) found.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n    fi\n    echo \"\" >> \"$report_file\"\n}\n\n# Function to perform integrity checks (hashing)\nperform_integrity_checks() {\n    local slug=\"$1\"\n    local skill_files_dir=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/artifact_bundle\"\n    local report_file=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n    local scratch_dir=$(create_scratch_dir \"$slug\")\n    local hash_log=\"${scratch_dir}/integrity_hashes.log\"\n\n    log \"Performing integrity checks for ${slug}...\"\n    echo \"#### Integrity Checks (Hashing)\" >> \"$report_file\"\n\n    # Find all files (excluding .git and potentially large binary files if known)\n    # and calculate their SHA256 sums.\n    if [ ! -d \"$skill_files_dir\" ] || [ -z \"$(ls -A \"$skill_files_dir\")\" ]; then\n        warn \"Skill files for ${slug} not found or empty at ${skill_files_dir}. Skipping integrity checks.\"\n        echo \"Skill files not found or empty. Skipping integrity checks.\" >> \"$report_file\"\n        return\n    fi\n\n    # Use `find` to get files, then `sha256sum`\n    # Using xargs -0 to handle filenames with spaces or special characters\n    if find \"$skill_files_dir\" -type f -print0 | xargs -0 sha256sum > \"$hash_log\"; then\n        if [ -s \"$hash_log\" ]; then\n            echo \"SHA256 hashes of key files (relative paths):\" >> \"$report_file\"\n            echo '```' >> \"$report_file\"\n            # Log hashes relative to the skill files directory for easier review\n            (cd \"$skill_files_dir\" && sha256sum $(find . -type f -not -path './.git/*' -not -name '*.jpg' -not -name '*.png' -not -name '*.gif' -not -name '*.webp' -not -name '*.mp4' -not -name '*.mov' | sed 's|^\\./||')) >> \"$hash_log\"\n            cat \"$hash_log\" | sed \"s|${skill_files_"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":21715,"output":4908,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26623,"cost":{"input":-21715,"output":-4908,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-26623}},"stopReason":"length","timestamp":1772143819026}}
