{"type":"message","id":"20b1b69e","parentId":"606a172e","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:11:24.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing script instructions**\n\nI need to give clear instructions for saving and running the script. First, I’ll emphasize making it executable, placing it in the home directory, and setting the MV-SKILL path. The script we’re discussing is called vet-clawhub-skill.sh, and I should mention how to run it with arguments, like bash vet-clawhub-skill.sh traffic-data. I'll also point out the need to install dependencies and check permissions, using chmod +x. Let's keep it concise!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Great. Here’s how to execute the malware-vetting script you got earlier.\n\nWhat you should have\n- The script file saved as vet-clawhub-skill.sh (or whichever name you chose).\n- It assumes:\n  - clawhub CLI is installed and accessible in PATH.\n  - You have a workspace under ~/inspection/workspace for artifacts.\n  - The OpenClaw root is at ~/.openclaw (adjust if yours is different).\n\nStep-by-step to run it\n1) Save the script\n- If you haven’t already, save the script content to:\n/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/vet-clawhub-skill.sh\n\n2) Make it executable\n- chmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/vet-clawhub-skill.sh\n\n3) Run with a target slug\n- To vet a single skill (e.g., traffic-data):\n  /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/vet-clawhub-skill.sh traffic-data\n\n- If you want to vet multiple slugs in one go, you can pass them in sequence:\n  /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/vet-clawhub-skill.sh traffic-data openclaw-safety-coach\n\n4) What to expect\n- The script will:\n  - Run clawhub inspect <slug> and place outputs in ~/inspection/workspace/<slug>/\n  - Perform a static grep-based scan for red flags\n  - Attempt a basic dependency review if manifest files exist\n  - Generate a findings markdown file at ~/inspection/workspace/<slug>/findings_<slug>.md\n\n5) Inspect the findings\n- Open the findings file to review results:\n  less ~/inspection/workspace/traffic-data/findings_traffic-data.md\n\nTips\n- If clawhub requires authentication, ensure you’re logged in (clawhub login) before running.\n- If you see permission prompts or errors, run the script with a user that has access to the local filesystem and the necessary binaries.\n- You can customize CODE_EXTENSIONS or SUSPICIOUS_PATTERNS inside the script if you want tighter/looser checks.\n\nWant me to tailor the exact command line to your environment (e.g., adjust paths) or add a small wrapper to loop over a list of slugs from a file?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":3765,"output":792,"cacheRead":20608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25165,"cost":{"input":-3765,"output":-792,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-4557}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772143878576}}
