{"type":"message","id":"8ae0527f","parentId":"16b962a8","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:14:30.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning script modifications**\n\nI need to come up with a plan and maybe adjust the script to output only \"Safe\" or \"Unsafe.\" I think I can modify mv-vet.sh to set exit codes: 0 for Safe and 1 for Unsafe. A minimal approach would be to run checks and determine if there's any high risk—if so, it should return Unsafe; otherwise, Safe.\n\nI’ll propose a small wrapper for mv-vet.sh that returns 0 if there are no high-risk findings and 1 if there are. Plus, since the user wants only \"Safe\" or \"Unsafe,\" I can provide a patch snippet for the script to print that based on findings.**Simplifying risk analysis**\n\nTo streamline things, if findings_<slug>.md contains \"HIGH RISK,\" \"install safely,\" or \"BLOCK,\" we can parse that information. After running analyses, it would be robust to check for \"HIGH RISK\" or \"WARNING:\" in the report. \n\nTo make it foolproof, I should implement a local variable called risk_found, initially set to false. If any \"SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND\" appear, I'll set risk_found to true and print \"Unsafe.\" At the end, if risk_found is true, I'll echo \"Unsafe,\" otherwise \"Safe.\" I'll provide an inline snippet for those modifications, ensuring no extra text.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here’s a simple way to get mv-vet to output only Safe or Unsafe.\n\nIdea:\n- Track a risk flag during the run.\n- If any high-risk signal is found, print Unsafe and exit with a non-zero code.\n- If nothing risky is found, print Safe and exit with code 0.\n- Output is exactly one word: Safe or Unsafe.\n\nOption A: Quick patch you can apply to mv-vet.sh (minimally invasive)\n- Add a global flag at top and a final print.\n\nInsert near the top (after other requires):\n- unsafe_found=0\n\nIn the static_analysis function, when you detect a risk, set the flag. For example, after appending the static scan results, you can set:\n- if grep -q \"SUSPICIOUS\" \"${slug_dir}/static_scan.log\"; then unsafe_found=1; fi\nOr, more simply, whenever you detect ANY suspicious pattern, set the flag.\n\nAt the very end of main() after all slugs are processed, emit the simplified result per slug:\n- if [ \"$unsafe_found\" -eq 0 ]; then echo \"Safe\"; else echo \"Unsafe\"; fi\n\nBut since mv-vet currently handles multiple slugs in a loop, you’ll want per-slug output. A compact per-slug wrapper:\n\nProposed per-slug end-of-loop addition (inside main’s loop, after generate_report for each slug):\n- if grep -q -i \"HIGH RISK\\|SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND\\|WARNING\" \"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"; then\n-   echo \"Unsafe\"\n-   exit 1\n- else\n-   echo \"Safe\"\n- fi\n\nNotes:\n- This prints exactly Safe or Unsafe for each slug and exits on the first Unsafe to avoid clutter.\n- If you want a per-slug, non-terminating output (Safe/Unsafe for every slug, but continue processing others), remove exit 1 and instead print Safe/Unsafe per slug and continue.\n\nOption B: Quick, minimal implementation (no patching)\n- After mv-vet finishes, run a tiny wrapper to convert the Markdown findings into a simple verdict:\n  - If the findings_<slug>.md contains any of: HIGH RISK, SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND, WARNING, then Unsafe; else Safe.\n  - You can run this as a post-step: for slug in traffic-data openclaw-safety-coach; do if grep -qiE \"HIGH RISK|SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND|WARNING\" ~/inspection/workspace/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md; then echo \"${slug}: Unsafe\"; else echo \"${slug}: Safe\"; fi; done\n\nWhat would you like me to do:\n- I can provide a concrete, ready-to-paste patch for mv-vet.sh to implement Safe/Unsafe per slug.\n- Or I can supply a tiny wrapper script (mv-vet-scan-guard.sh) that runs mv-vet for slugs and prints Safe/Unsafe per slug without modifying mv-vet.sh.\n\nTell me which option you prefer and the exact path you want the patch to be applied (default: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":2329,"output":1360,"cacheRead":24832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28521,"cost":{"input":-2329,"output":-1360,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-3689}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772144058999}}
