{"type":"message","id":"b9291a8c","parentId":"30680736","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:15:35.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning mv-vet.sh Patch**\n\nI need to outline how to enhance the mv-vet.sh script by adding per-slug output indicating \"Safe\" or \"Unsafe,\" without exiting on danger. I'll offer a code snippet to show where to make modifications in the main loop, specifically after the generate_report section. I should include a new function called verdict_for_slug, which will check the findings file for keywords and print the status accordingly. Additionally, I'll mention the option to collect results to a file. Keeping this succinct is essential!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here’s a minimal, ready-to-paste patch to mv-vet.sh that makes output per slug non-terminating and prints Safe or Unsafe for each slug without exiting the loop.\n\nWhat this does\n- After generating the findings_<slug>.md for each slug, it checks that file for risk indicators.\n- Prints: \"<slug>: Safe\" or \"<slug>: Unsafe\" on its own line.\n- Does not exit the script on Unsafe; it continues to the next slug.\n\nPatch to mv-vet.sh (insert and adjust as needed)\n\n1) Add a simple verdict function (place near other helper functions, e.g., after log()/warn()):\n\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# ... existing content ...\n\nverdict_for_slug() {\n  local slug=\"$1\"\n  local report=\"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n\n  # Default to Safe if no report exists\n  if [ ! -f \"${report}\" ]; then\n    echo \"${slug}: Safe\"\n    return 0\n  fi\n\n  if grep -qiE \"HIGH RISK|SUSPICIOUS PATTERNS FOUND|WARNING\" \"${report}\"; then\n    echo \"${slug}: Unsafe\"\n  else\n    echo \"${slug}: Safe\"\n  fi\n}\n\n2) Call verdict_for_slug inside the main loop, after generate_report (and do not exit on Unsafe):\n\nReplace or augment the end of the per-slug block:\n\n  main() {\n    check_prereqs\n\n    if [ \"$#\" -lt 1 ]; then\n      usage\n      exit 1\n    fi\n\n    local slug\n    for slug in \"$@\"; do\n      info \"Starting vet for ${slug}\"\n      inspect_slug \"${slug}\"\n      static_analysis \"${slug}\"\n      dependencies_review \"${slug}\"\n      integrity_checks \"${slug}\"\n      generate_report \"${slug}\"\n      info \"Completed vet for ${slug}. Findings at ${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/${slug}/findings_${slug}.md\"\n\n      # NEW: per-slug verdict output (non-terminating)\n      verdict_for_slug \"${slug}\"\n    done\n  }\n\n3) If you want to accumulate all verdicts in a file as well, append:\n\n  verdict_for_slug \"${slug}\" >> \"${INSPECTION_BASE_DIR}/all_verdicts.txt\" 2>&1 || true\n\nTips\n- Output format: exactly \"slug: Safe\" or \"slug: Unsafe\" per line.\n- If you want to suppress output for some slugs, wrap verdict_for_slug call in a guard.\n- This keeps your MV-VET script backwards-compatible for other steps.\n\nWould you like me to apply this patch directly to your mv-vet.sh file here, or provide a clean diff you can patch yourself? Also tell me the exact path you want me to target (default: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/malware-vet/)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":745,"output":891,"cacheRead":27136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28772,"cost":{"input":-745,"output":-891,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1636}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772144129242}}
