{"type":"message","id":"782cf5b4","parentId":"6f7e5d68","timestamp":"2026-02-26T22:20:41.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I patched mv-vet.sh to add a robust guard, but you’re still seeing an “ext: unbound variable” error when running on smart-route. That means the static analysis path is hitting the code path that builds or uses ext_args even when CODE_EXTENSIONS is empty.\n\nWhat I’ll do next\n- Strengthen the static_analysis block to be absolutely robust when CODE_EXTENSIONS is empty:\n  - Initialize ext_args as an empty array unconditionally.\n  - Only build and use ext_args if CODE_EXTENSIONS has at least one entry.\n  - Avoid any stray references to an undefined ext variable.\n\nPlan:\n- Update the static_analysis function to:\n  - ext_args=()\n  - if [ \"${#CODE_EXTENSIONS[@]}\" -gt 0 ]; then for ext in \"${CODE_EXTENSIONS[@]}\"; do ext_args+=( -iname \"*.${ext}\" ); done; fi\n  - if [ \"${#ext_args[@]}\" -gt 0 ]; then run the find/xargs grep path; else skip static scan gracefully.\n\nI can push the fix and re-run mv-vet on smart-route (and any other slugs you want). Do you want me to proceed with:\n- A quick patch-and-retest on just smart-route, then\n- A batch run on additional slugs (e.g., traffic-data, openclaw-safety-coach) after confirming the fix?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":269,"output":1089,"cacheRead":34048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35406,"cost":{"input":-269,"output":-1089,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1358}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772144435427}}
